    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(S.T.) Die lune, Vl kal marcii, fuit manifestus <persName><name
                                ref="Andreas">Andrea</name></persName> f. <persName><name ref="Wido"
                                >Vuidonis</name></persName> quod fuit ibi ubi domna <rs
                            key="#Abbesses">abbatissa</rs><persName key="#Abbesses"><name
                                ref="Adhelasia"> Adelasia </name></persName><orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/53">S. Sixti
                        </orgName>investivit <persName><name ref="Ermengarda"
                            >Hermengardam</name></persName> uxorem <persName
                            key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus"><name ref="Heinricus"
                            >Henrici</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldi</rs> per <rs key="#Feudum"
                            >feodum</rs> in se et in heredibus suis masculis et feminis nominative
                        ex omnibus rebus in illis territoriis quas tenebat per feodum ab ipso <rs
                            key="#Monasteries"> monasterio</rs>. Item ipse Andrea dixit quod fuit in
                        loco ubi <persName key="#Abbesses"><name ref="Febronia"
                            >Febronia</name></persName> investivit <name ref="Azo"><persName
                                key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">Azonem</persName></name> f. Henrici et<persName>
                            <name ref="Adhelasia">Adelasiam </name>filiam eius</persName> per
                        parabolam iamscripte Hermengarde per feodum in se et in heredibus eorum ex
                        iamscripto feodo S. Sixti masculis et feminis,<persName>
                            <name ref="Folco">Fulco</name> de Ripalta </persName>similiter dixit.
                                <persName><name ref="Coneradus">Conradus</name> Batitor</persName>
                        et <persName><name ref="Burgundius">Burgundius</name></persName> f. eius
                        similiter dixerunt. MCXL, ind. IV. Azo gastaldus fecit scribere totum hoc
                        quod tenebat per feodum a monasterio S. Sixti. Feodum ipsius monasterii est
                        totam terram quam tenet infra <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/43"
                            >civitatem</placeName> ipse Azo * * * et in <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Production #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_individuals #Feudum"
                            ref="#places/14"><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Production #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Outflow #Allocation_to_individuals #Feudum"
                                ref="#estates/76">capite Trebie</geogName></placeName> sunt <rs
                            key="#Production">clausure</rs> quattuor in <placeName>capite
                            Burgi</placeName> quibus coheret intermedio terra <rs
                            key="#Local_elites">Advocatorum</rs> et<persName><name ref="Teudo">
                                Teitonis </name></persName>et <rs key="#Clusae/gates">clausi</rs>
                        duo <rs key="#Wine">vineÄ™</rs> ibi prope et adheret eis intermedio terra
                        ipsius monasterii que fuit recupata a <rs key="#Local_elites">Muglariis</rs>
                        et <persName><name ref="Grimerius">Grimerio </name>Marasco</persName> et
                            <placeName key="#Areas">Salicetus</placeName> iuxta vineam totum usque
                        in lavanderio sed via divit vinea a Saliceto et * * * terre quam tenet ultra
                            <placeName key="#Areas">Raganella in Mediano</placeName> et<rs
                            key="#Petiae"> peciam</rs> I in <placeName key="#Areas"
                            >Vignale</placeName>, <rs key="#Production">campum</rs> I prope
                            <placeName ref="#places/2491" key="#Areas">Fontanam</placeName> que
                        tenet mod. III<rs key="#Cereals #Maiores"> frumenti</rs>, campum I ultra
                        stradam que vadit ad <placeName ref="#places/70" key="#Burgi"
                            >Kalendascum</placeName> et fit rectum et laboratum per <persName><name
                                ref="Hencantatus">Hencantatum</name></persName> cum terra
                                <persName><name ref="Gherardus">Gerardi</name> de Areno
                        </persName>et <persName><name ref="Gherardus">Gerardi
                                </name></persName><persName><name ref="Ermizo"
                            >Hermizoni</name></persName> adheret et <rs key="#Local_elites"
                            >Iniquitatis</rs> et filiorum <persName><name ref="Uualengus"
                                >Vualengi</name></persName> et <rs key="#Production_units">braidam
                        </rs>I magnam que tenet magis XX mod. frumenti. Coheret eu <rs
                            key="#Production">terra</rs> filiorum <persName><name ref="Rainerius"
                                >Rainerii</name></persName> et filiorum <persName><name
                                ref="Gherardus">Gerardi</name> de Curte Maiore</persName> et
                        Iniquitatis et via de capite Trebie usque ad crucem, iterum alia pecia ibi
                        prone que tenet caput in via iuxta terram Iniquitatis ad alium campum quem
                        teneo ab Iniquitate et iuxta illam quam datam habeo iamdicto monasterio pro
                        anima patris mei et Gerardi de Arena et <rs key="#Production">clausum </rs>I
                        quod tenet <persName key="#Abbots"><name ref="Bucca"
                            >Bucca</name></persName><rs key="#Abbots"> abatis</rs> et
                                <persName><name ref="Ribaldus">Ribaldus</name></persName>. In
                            <placeName key="#Areas">campo Adone</placeName> peciam I quam
                                <persName><name ref="Benedictus">Benedictus</name></persName> de
                        strada levata ed <persName><name ref="Bernardus">Bernardus</name></persName>
                        f. eius tenent. Item II pecias terre quas<persName><name ref="Centenarius">
                                Centenarius</name></persName> tenet, una iacet ultra <orgName
                            key="#Churches">S. Iohannem</orgName> et <persName><name ref="Gherardus"
                                >Gerardi</name></persName> et via, alia ad<placeName
                            key="#Geography"> Falgeriam </placeName>cui terra <persName><name
                                ref="Albericus">Alberici</name></persName> filii <persName><name
                                ref="Hugo">Ugonis</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Uilielmus">Vuilielmi</name> de Carido</persName> et <rs
                            key="#Rivers">Trebia</rs> adheret. Item iugum I terre quam tenet
                            <persName>Albericus</persName> f. <persName><name ref="Agino">Aginonis
                            </name></persName>in <placeName key="#Geography">Rimilierio</placeName>
                        iuxta filios <persName><name ref="Azo">Azonis</name> Pallastrelli</persName>
                        et <persName><name ref="Burningus">Burnengi</name> de Ripalta
                        </persName></ab>
                </div>
